A single-page website exploring how Christmas is experienced by people with different physical abilities (deaf, blind, mute, and a fourth perspective). The goal is to celebrate diverse sensory experiences of Christmas — warm and inclusive, not clinical.
Layout:
Screen divided into 4 distinct sections (quadrant grid preferred), each representing one experience. Sections should feel distinct but visually connected — unified by a central glowing element or shared design language.
Mood: Celebratory, warm, intimate
Color Palette:

Wine Burgundy: #722F37
Festive Gold: #D4AF37
Forest Sage: #4A5D4A
Warm Ivory: #F5EBE0
Deep Brown (text): #3D2914

Typography:

Headers: Cormorant Garamond (Google Fonts)
Body: Atkinson Hyperlegible (Google Fonts)

*Some Pointers to keep in mind*
- It should be highly optimized for mobiles because most people will use it there itself. 